# TrainDart — Cursor rules

## Privacy & compliance (GDPR / ePrivacy)

- All frontend changes must respect the **GDPR** and **ePrivacy Directive**.
- Do not add non-essential cookies, local storage, fingerprinting, or third-party trackers without an explicit, informed user choice.
- Prefer privacy-by-default: essential functionality only until consent is given where required.

## Cookie consent

- Any new feature involving **tracking, analytics, advertising, or non-essential data collection** MUST be integrated with the project's **CookieConsent** logic before shipping.
- Do not load third-party scripts (e.g. Google Analytics) until the user has opted in via CookieConsent.
- When adding a new data-collecting integration, wire it to the same consent categories and document what is stored and why.

## Bot prevention

- Always implement **honeypot fields** on **public forms** (registration, contact, password reset, guest flows, etc.) for bot prevention.
- Honeypots must be hidden from users (off-screen or equivalent), excluded from tab order, and validated server-side; reject submissions silently or with a generic error—never reveal the honeypot mechanism.

## Legal documents

- If modifying **user data handling** (what is collected, how it is used, shared, retained, or processed—including AI, analytics, IP logging, or third-party services), ensure **Terms of Service** and **Privacy Policy** content and i18n (`resources/js/lang/{en,lv}/legal.json`) are updated to match.
- Registration and other consent surfaces must remain linked to the current Terms and Privacy pages.
